<collectingRegion box="[1400,1436,224,248]" country="Maldives" name="Uthuru" pageId="9">nOt</collectingRegion>
exceeding eyes); rOstrum with three spines, being the central spine slightly larger than the Others (
<figureCitation box="[1280,1379,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1843,1865]" captionTargetBox="[225,1365,589,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[225,1365,589,1824]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pontophilus brevirostris Smith, 1881, female (TL: 61 mm), Potiguar Basin, MT–61. A. Habitus: dorsal view. B. Telson and uropods (MOUFPE:15.245).Scales bar = A = 5 mm, B, C = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1135548/files/figure.png" pageId="9">Fig. 8 A</figureCitation>
