<emphasis box="[874,897,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="9">vs</emphasis>
. Only One spine, 2 spines). AccOrding tO 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" pageId="9" refString="Smith, S. I. (1882) Reports on the results of dredging, under the supervision of Alexander Agassiz, on the East Coast of the United States, during the summer of 1880, by the U. S. Coast Survey Steamer &quot; Blake, &quot; Commander J. R. Bartlett, U. S. N., Commanding. XVII. - Report on the Crustacea. Part I. Decapoda. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 10, 1 - 104." type="journal article" year="1882">Smith (1882)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[241,545,404,429]" pageId="9" refString="Williams, A. B. &amp; Wigley, R. L. (1977) Distribution of decapod Crustacea off Northeastern United States based on specimens at the Northeast Fisheries Center, Woods Hole, Massachusetts. NOAA Technical Reports, NMFS circular 407, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="1977">Williams &amp; Wigley (1977)</bibRefCitation>
